Class SimpleHashtable<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.oop.lab4.prob2.SimpleHashtable<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - type of argument for key.
    V - type of argument for value.

    public class SimpleHashtable<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
    The SimpleHashtable class represents a hash table used to implement an associative array, a structure that can map keys to values.

    A hash table uses a hash function to compute an index into an array of slots, from which the desired value can be found.

    Author:
    Jurij Kos
